1. Tress are non-linear hierarchical data structures
2. Root -> head of the tree
3. Children 
4. Lead nodes -> who doesn't have any children
5. Sub tree 
6. Ancestores -> parent and grand parents 


Types of binary trees:
1. Full Binary Tree - every node has 0 or 2 childrens
2. Complete binary Tree - all levels are completely filled except the last level and last level is filled as left as possible
3. Perfect binary tree - all leaf nodes are at same level
4. Balanced binary tree - height of the tree is at max log(n)
5. Degenrate binary tree - skewed tree 

Representation:

struct Node {
	int data;
	Node *left;
	Node *right;

	Node(int val) {
		data = val;
		left = right = nullptr;
	}
};